headlines.description: — Grant Williams scored a career-high 25 points, Jaylen Brown had 27 and the Boston Celtics overcame the absence of leading scorer Jayson Tatum to extend their winning streak to nine games by beating the Toronto Raptors 106-104 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant Williams has career-high 25, Celtics' streak reaches 9

headlines.description: — Rui Hachimura equaled a career high with 30 points and Kyle Kuzma added 25 to lift the Washington Wizards to a 138-118 victory over the Orlando Magic on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hachimura scores 30 to lead Wizards over Magic 138-118

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier hit three throws with 1.1 seconds remaining, and the undermanned Charlotte Hornets overcame a 19-point, third-quarter deficit to end the Atlanta Hawks’ five-game winning streak with a 122-118 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier caps 19-point rally, Hornets end Hawks' 5-game streak

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored a season-high 44 points, D'Angelo Russell added 23 and the Minnesota Timberwolves handed the Houston Rockets their 13th straight loss with a 113-104 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 44; Wolves hand Rockets 13th straight loss

headlines.description: — The broad-shouldered Ish Wainright looks as if he should be making plays in the NFL instead of the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Okogie, Bridges lead short-handed Suns past Pacers 112-107

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 15 of his 32 points in the third quarter and the Philadelphia 76ers, playing without Joel Embiid and James Harden, completed a perfect five-game road trip by beating the Sacramento Kings 129-127 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers, without Embiid and Harden, edge Kings for 5-0 trip
